"records at large" / servermanage

Beware: this project is in a very early stage! It should work.


Prerequisites:
* Python
* Django (http://www.djangoproject.com)
* Python DB-Drivers (see Django)
* powerdnsd

Installation:

create settings.py (you can use settings_example.py as an example).
* Change DATABASE-Stuff to match your Setup.
* CHANGE SECRET_KEY!

Create the database:
./manage.py syncdb


Configure powerdnsd:
Hint:

launch=gpgsql

gpgsql-dbname=servermanage
gpgsql-user=servermanage
gpgsql-password=secret
gpgsql-host=127.0.0.1 


It should work.
